Data Transforming and Formatting 8

Format and adding column  'Country '

- Select value column ,  go to column tool > Change format decimal number and change decimal value to 1 

- Select the 'Port Code' column > Column Tool> Summarization = 'Don't Summarize' 

- Go to  Home  > Transform Data  > Add Column > Conditional Column > New Column Name  ' Country'> Column Name 'Border'> Value ' Border' > Output 'USA' 

- Then Ok > Close Apply 


Marge and Transform Columns 

- Go  to Home > Transform Data > transform data 

- select 3 columns  ' Port Name'  , 'State' and  ' Country' > Merge column > New column Name = Port 

- Apply and save 

- Select column 'Port' > Column Tool > Data category = Place  

- Save everything 



Data transformation in  Power BI ; Easy tips , Watch

 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6g4PKRHC1UQ
